### Smart Publish 
Publishes the selected item if it has changed since the last time it was published. When you run Smart Publish, the selected item in the Master database is compared with the equivalent item in the target database (web or pub) and, if the item has changed, it is published. When you are publishing single items, Smart Publish is a quick way to make sure that all changes to a specific item and its sub items are published.

### Republish
Publishes everything. Republish overwrites the selected item in the target (web or pub) database with the equivalent item from the Master database – even if it has not changed. 

### Publish related items
If this box is checked, all related items are then added to the publishing queue. By default, it returns the following items related to the item being published:

- The item's clones
- Any media used by the item
- All items the published item links to

***This is not our recommended publishing approach.***

### Publishing Languages
As a Distributor you will only have access to the language versions that are available on your website. Ensure the appropriate checkboxes are checked for the language versions you are updating.
